# 🛍️ Shopify Sales & Customer Analysis Dashboard

## 📌 Project Overview

This project involved developing an interactive Power BI dashboard to analyze Shopify order-line data for an online footwear and accessories store.

The dashboard focuses on revenue performance, product performance, payment gateway usage, order trends, and key business KPIs.

---

## 🎯 Project Objective

The main objectives were to:

- Analyze overall Shopify revenue.
- Identify top-performing product types.
- Analyze order volume by payment gateway.
- Track average order value and tax collected.
- Study short-term sales trends.
- Build an interactive dashboard for business performance monitoring.

---

## 📂 Dataset

The dataset, `Shopify_Sales.xlsx`, contained:

- 7,431 order-line records
- 19 fields

Important fields included:

- Order Number
- Billing Address
- Currency
- Customer ID
- Invoice Date
- Gateway
- Product Type
- Quantity
- Subtotal Price
- Total Price (USD)
- Total Tax

A data terminology reference was also reviewed to understand technical fields such as Gateway, Variant ID, and Admin GraphQL API ID.

---

## 🛠 Tools & Technologies

- Power BI
- Power Query
- DAX
- Data Modeling
- Data Visualization

